  <style>
    *,*::before,*::after{box-sizing:border-box;margin:0;padding:0}
    :root{
      --sans:'Inter',-apple-system,sans-serif;
      --mono:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;
      --bg:#080c0a;--bg-2:#0c110f;--bg-3:#111916;
      --g:#00c864;--g-dim:rgba(0,200,100,.06);--g-b:rgba(0,200,100,.18);
      --border:rgba(255,255,255,.07);
      --text:#f1f5f9;--text-2:#cbd5e1;--text-3:#94a3b8;--text-4:#64748b;
      --red:#ef4444;--amber:#f59e0b;--r:8px
    }
    body{font-family:var(--sans);background:var(--bg);color:var(--text);line-height:1.7;-webkit-font-smoothing:antialiased}
    a{color:var(--g);text-decoration:none}a:hover{text-decoration:underline}
    /* Breadcrumb */
    .bc{max-width:900px;margin:0 auto;padding:14px 24px 0;font-family:var(--mono);font-size:11px;color:var(--text-4);display:flex;gap:6px;align-items:center}
    .bc a{color:var(--text-4);text-decoration:none}.bc a:hover{color:var(--g)}
    /* Hero */
    .hero{padding:64px 24px 52px;background:var(--bg)}
    .hero-inner{max-width:760px;margin:0 auto}
    .tag{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:10px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:.12em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--g);background:var(--g-dim);border:1px solid var(--g-b);padding:4px 12px;border-radius:4px;display:inline-block;margin-bottom:22px}
    .hero h1{font-size:clamp(34px,5.5vw,54px);font-weight:900;letter-spacing:-.04em;line-height:1.04;color:var(--text);margin-bottom:8px}
    .hero-role{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:12px;color:var(--g);letter-spacing:.08em;margin-bottom:22px;display:flex;align-items:center;gap:10px}
    .hero-role::before{content:'';display:inline-block;width:6px;height:6px;border-radius:50%;background:var(--g);animation:ping 2.2s ease-in-out infinite}
    @keyframes ping{0%,100%{opacity:1}50%{opacity:.3}}
    .hero-lead{font-size:17px;color:var(--text-3);line-height:1.85;margin-bottom:32px;max-width:640px}
    /* Credential strip */
    .cred-strip{display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:8px}
    .cred{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:10px;color:var(--text-4);border:1px solid var(--border);background:var(--bg-2);padding:6px 12px;border-radius:4px;display:flex;align-items:center;gap:6px;white-space:nowrap}
    .cred-dot{width:5px;height:5px;border-radius:50%;background:var(--g);flex-shrink:0}
    .cred-link{color:var(--text-4);text-decoration:none}.cred-link:hover{color:var(--g);text-decoration:none}
    /* Sections */
    .section{padding:60px 24px;background:var(--bg)}
    .section-alt{padding:60px 24px;background:var(--bg-2)}
    .inner{max-width:760px;margin:0 auto}
    .sec-tag{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:10px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:.14em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--text-4);margin-bottom:12px}
    h2{font-size:clamp(20px,3vw,26px);font-weight:800;letter-spacing:-.025em;color:var(--text);margin-bottom:16px;line-height:1.2}
    p{font-size:15px;color:var(--text-3);line-height:1.85;margin-bottom:16px}
    p:last-child{margin-bottom:0}
    strong{color:var(--text)}
    /* Expertise grid */
    .exp-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:12px;margin-top:28px}
    .exp-card{border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:var(--r);padding:20px 22px;background:var(--bg-3)}
    .exp-label{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:9px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:.14em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--g);margin-bottom:8px}
    .exp-title{font-size:14px;font-weight:700;color:var(--text);margin-bottom:6px;line-height:1.3}
    .exp-body{font-size:13px;color:var(--text-3);line-height:1.65}
    .exp-body a{color:var(--g);text-decoration:underline;text-underline-offset:2px}
    /* Methodology */
    .methodology{border:1px solid var(--g-b);background:var(--g-dim);border-radius:var(--r);padding:26px 30px;margin-top:28px}
    .methodology-label{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:10px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:.14em;color:var(--g);margin-bottom:16px;text-transform:uppercase}
    .methodology p{font-size:14px;color:var(--text-3);line-height:1.75;margin-bottom:20px}
    .method-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:10px}
    .m-item{background:rgba(0,0,0,.35);border-radius:6px;padding:14px 16px;border:1px solid rgba(0,200,100,.08)}
    .m-source{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:11px;font-weight:700;color:var(--g);margin-bottom:4px}
    .m-desc{font-size:12px;color:var(--text-4);line-height:1.55}
    /* Transparency */
    .transparency{border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:var(--r);background:var(--bg-3);overflow:hidden;margin-top:28px}
    .t-row{display:flex;gap:16px;align-items:flex-start;padding:18px 22px;border-bottom:1px solid var(--border)}
    .t-row:last-child{border-bottom:none}
    .t-icon{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:14px;color:var(--g);flex-shrink:0;width:22px;padding-top:1px}
    .t-text{font-size:14px;color:var(--text-3);line-height:1.7}
    .t-text strong{color:var(--text)}
    .t-text a{color:var(--g)}
    /* Tools */
    .tools-list{display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:8px;margin-top:24px}
    .tool-row{display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;gap:12px;padding:14px 18px;border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:var(--r);background:var(--bg-3);text-decoration:none;transition:border-color .18s}
    .tool-row:hover{border-color:var(--g-b);text-decoration:none}
    .tool-name{font-size:14px;font-weight:600;color:var(--text)}
    .tool-saving{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:11px;color:var(--g);white-space:nowrap}
    /* Contact */
    .contact-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:12px;margin-top:24px}
    .contact-card{border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:var(--r);padding:18px 20px;background:var(--bg-3)}
    .contact-label{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:9px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:.14em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--text-4);margin-bottom:10px}
    .contact-link{font-size:14px;font-weight:600;color:var(--g);text-decoration:none}
    .contact-link:hover{text-decoration:underline}
    .contact-desc{font-size:12px;color:var(--text-4);margin-top:5px;line-height:1.5}
    /* CTA strip */
    .cta-strip{background:var(--bg-3);border-top:1px solid var(--border);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border);padding:40px 24px}
    .cta-inner{max-width:760px;margin:0 auto;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;gap:24px;flex-wrap:wrap}
    .cta-text h3{font-size:18px;font-weight:800;color:var(--text);margin-bottom:6px;letter-spacing:-.02em}
    .cta-text p{font-size:14px;color:var(--text-3);margin:0}
    .btn{display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:8px;font-family:var(--sans);font-size:14px;font-weight:700;padding:13px 26px;border-radius:var(--r);background:var(--g);color:#020617;text-decoration:none;transition:opacity .2s,transform .2s;white-space:nowrap}
    .btn:hover{opacity:.88;transform:translateY(-1px);text-decoration:none}
    @media(max-width:640px){
      .exp-grid,.method-grid,.contact-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr}
      .hero{padding:44px 16px 36px}
      .section,.section-alt{padding:44px 16px}
      .cta-inner{flex-direction:column;align-items:flex-start}
    }
  </style>
  <script async src="https://www.googletagmanager.com/gtag/js?id=G-TE6Z6CW514"></script>
  <script>window.dataLayer=window.dataLayer||[];function gtag(){dataLayer.push(arguments);}gtag('js',new Date());gtag('config','G-TE6Z6CW514');</script>
  </head>
<body>
<Nav />

<div class="bc">
  <a href="/">Home</a>
  <span style="opacity:.4">/</span>
  <span style="color:var(--text-3)">About</span>
</div>

<main id="main-content">

  <!-- ── HERO ── -->
  <div class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <div class="tag">About the author</div>
      <h1>Luke</h1>
      <div class="hero-role">Shopify Automation Specialist &nbsp;·&nbsp; Founder, Stack Architect</div>
      <p class="hero-lead">I build and document free, open-source automation tools for Shopify store owners. Every guide on this site comes from hands-on implementation work — building Make.com scenarios, configuring server-side tracking APIs, and testing every build hands-on before it's published. The same architecture that Elevar charges $300/month and Triple Whale charges $129/month for — released here free, with the full source on GitHub, step-by-step setup, and no upsell.</p>
      <div class="cred-strip">
        <div class="cred"><span class="cred-dot"></span>Shopify automation specialist</div>
        <div class="cred"><span class="cred-dot"></span>Make.com · Meta CAPI · Google Enhanced Conversions</div>
        <div class="cred"><span class="cred-dot"></span>Open-source · No subscription · No upsell</div>
        <div class="cred"><span class="cred-dot"></span>Based in the UK</div>
        <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/luke-stackarchitect" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="cred cred-link">
          <svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" style="color:var(--g);flex-shrink:0"><path d="M16 8a6 6 0 0 1 6 6v7h-4v-7a2 2 0 0 0-2-2 2 2 0 0 0-2 2v7h-4v-7a6 6 0 0 1 6-6z"/><rect x="2" y="9" width="4" height="12"/><circle cx="4" cy="4" r="2"/></svg>
          LinkedIn
        </a>
        <a href="https://github.com/lsb11/stackarchitect" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="cred cred-link">
          <svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor" style="color:var(--g);flex-shrink:0"><path d="M12 .5C5.7.5.5 5.7.5 12c0 5.1 3.3 9.4 7.9 10.9.6.1.8-.2.8-.5v-2c-3.2.7-3.9-1.4-3.9-1.4-.5-1.3-1.3-1.7-1.3-1.7-1.1-.7.1-.7.1-.7 1.2.1 1.8 1.2 1.8 1.2 1 1.8 2.7 1.3 3.4 1 .1-.7.4-1.3.7-1.6-2.6-.3-5.3-1.3-5.3-5.7 0-1.3.5-2.3 1.2-3.1-.1-.3-.5-1.5.1-3.1 0 0 1-.3 3.3 1.2a11.5 11.5 0 0 1 6 0c2.3-1.5 3.3-1.2 3.3-1.2.6 1.6.2 2.8.1 3.1.8.8 1.2 1.8 1.2 3.1 0 4.4-2.7 5.4-5.3 5.7.4.4.8 1.1.8 2.2v3.3c0 .3.2.6.8.5 4.6-1.5 7.9-5.8 7.9-10.9C23.5 5.7 18.3.5 12 .5z"/></svg>
          GitHub
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ── BACKGROUND ── -->
  <section class="section-alt">
    <div class="inner">
      <div class="sec-tag">// Background &amp; experience</div>
      <h2>Where this knowledge comes from</h2>
      <p>Stack Architect exists because of a pattern I kept seeing in the Shopify ecosystem: store owners paying $149–$299/month for server-side tracking tools that do little more than route a <a href="https://shopify.dev/docs/api/admin-rest/2024-01/resources/webhook" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Shopify Order webhook</a> through an automation platform. I built the first version of CAPI Shield myself — configuring the <a href="https://developers.facebook.com/docs/marketing-api/conversions-api" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Meta Conversions API</a> directly via Make.com — and it sends the same server-side events to Meta that the paid tools do, at $0.</p>
      <p>That pattern repeated across every category. Inventory management. P&amp;L reporting. TikTok Events API. Email automation. In every case, the paid app was charging monthly for configuration work that takes under 10 minutes to replicate directly. So I documented all of it — step by step, with the exact API endpoints, field mappings, and Make.com scenario structures — and published it free.</p>
      <p>The full source for every tool is public on <a href="https://github.com/lsb11/stackarchitect" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a>, so nothing here is a black box. Anything I describe can be inspected, forked, and rebuilt independently — which is more than any of the paid alternatives offer.</p>
      <p><strong>Every number on this site is sourced or clearly framed.</strong> The Event Match Quality target (7+) is what well-matched server-side events typically achieve. Savings figures are calculated against current Shopify App Store pricing, checked regularly. Conversion-recovery percentages (20–40%) match published ranges from Meta's own CAPI documentation. No fabricated metrics. No purchased reviews. No manufactured social proof. If a number isn't backed by a source, it isn't here.</p>
      <p><strong>Featured in.</strong> I was interviewed by CTO Sync on <a href="https://ctosync.com/qa/deciding-when-engineering-teams-pay-down-technical-debt/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">deciding when engineering teams should pay down technical debt</a> — the same prioritisation thinking that shapes how the tools and guides here are built and maintained.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── EXPERTISE ── -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="inner">
      <div class="sec-tag">// Technical expertise</div>
      <h2>What I work with directly</h2>
      <p>The guides on this site cover areas I implement hands-on. Here is an honest breakdown of what I build and test directly:</p>
      <div class="exp-grid">
        <div class="exp-card">
          <div class="exp-label">Server-side tracking</div>
          <div class="exp-title">Meta CAPI &amp; Google Enhanced Conversions</div>
          <div class="exp-body">Direct implementation of <a href="https://developers.facebook.com/docs/marketing-api/conversions-api" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Meta Conversions API</a> and <a href="https://support.google.com/google-ads/answer/9888656" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Enhanced Conversions</a> via Make.com webhooks — configured to reach the high Event Match Quality (7+) that well-matched server-side events achieve.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="exp-card">
          <div class="exp-label">Automation</div>
          <div class="exp-title">Make.com &amp; Google Apps Script</div>
          <div class="exp-body">Building <a href="https://www.make.com/en/help/tools/webhooks" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Make.com scenarios</a> for Shopify webhook routing, multi-branch logic, error handling, and retry patterns. Diagnosing and fixing <a href="https://developers.google.com/apps-script/guides/services/quotas" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Apps Script quota errors</a> at volume.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="exp-card">
          <div class="exp-label">Inventory &amp; reporting</div>
          <div class="exp-title">Shopify Webhooks &amp; Google Sheets</div>
          <div class="exp-body">Real-time order logging to Google Sheets via <a href="https://shopify.dev/docs/api/admin-rest/2024-01/resources/webhook" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Shopify Order payment webhooks</a>. Live P&amp;L dashboards tracking revenue, COGS, ad spend, and net profit — no BI tool required.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="exp-card">
          <div class="exp-label">TikTok &amp; email</div>
          <div class="exp-title">TikTok Events API &amp; Systeme.io</div>
          <div class="exp-body">Server-side <a href="https://business-api.tiktok.com/portal/docs?id=1771100786590721" target="_blank" rel="noopener">TikTok Events API</a> via Make.com — built to recover the 20–40% of conversions iOS ITP strips from browser-only tracking. Replicating Klaviyo automations on Systeme.io's free plan with full parity.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── TRANSPARENCY ── -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="inner">
      <div class="sec-tag">// How this site works</div>
      <h2>Full transparency</h2>
      <div class="transparency">
        <div class="t-row">
          <div class="t-icon">$</div>
          <div class="t-text"><strong>Affiliate links fund this resource.</strong> Stack Architect uses affiliate links to Make.com, Systeme.io, Tidio, Gorgias, GetResponse, Beehiiv, and Google Workspace. If you sign up via a link on this site, I may earn a commission at no extra cost to you. I only recommend tools I use and have tested hands-on myself. Affiliate relationships do not influence which tools are recommended — if a free alternative exists, it is always listed first.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="t-row">
          <div class="t-icon">0</div>
          <div class="t-text"><strong>The tools are free forever.</strong> No tool on this site has a paid tier or will ever move behind a paywall. The <a href="/pro/">$29 Complete Kit</a> is a one-time purchase of pre-built files — four Make.com JSON blueprints and two Google Sheets templates — not a gated version of the free guides. Everything in the kit can be built manually from the free guides.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="t-row">
          <div class="t-icon">✓</div>
          <div class="t-text"><strong>Numbers are sourced or clearly framed.</strong> The Event Match Quality target (7+) reflects what well-matched server-side events achieve. Savings ranges reflect current Shopify App Store pricing, cross-referenced as of June 2026. Conversion-recovery percentages (20–40%) match published ranges from <a href="https://developers.facebook.com/docs/marketing-api/conversions-api/using-the-api" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Meta's own CAPI documentation</a>.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="t-row">
          <div class="t-icon">↗</div>
          <div class="t-text"><strong>External sources are cited throughout.</strong> Where guides reference API behaviour, platform documentation, or third-party specifications, the source is linked directly to the official documentation. Platform pricing and API behaviour change — always verify current details directly with the vendor before deployment.</div>
